Based on the question, "Is [child's name] covered by any kind of health insurance or some other kind of health care plan?" and a series of questions that seek to determine the health insurance coverage type for the child. Children are considered uninsured if they did not have private health insurance, Medicare, Medicaid, Children's Health Insurance Program (CHIP), a State-sponsored health plan, other government programs, or military health plan (includes TRICARE, VA, and CHAMP-VA) at the time of interview.
